Now you have to save this file as : CP.java (Don't forget to write CP with Capital Lettres!)
[b][u]
STEP 2[/u][/b]

When you are done with this, you will have to open your server.java file and in it you will need to add 2 things!

First search (CTRL + F) in [b]server.java[/b] for something like this:
[code]public static int ShutDownCounter = 0;[/code]

Under that you have to add this:
[code]public static CP CP = null;[/code]

Now we are almost ready, the only thing we have to do now is to add this at your [b]Public void run[/b]

Search for this in your [b]server.java[/b]
[code] public void run() {[/code]

Than you will see something like this:
[code]public void run() {
        // setup the listener
        try {
            shutdownClientHandler = false;
            clientListener = new java.net.ServerSocket(serverlistenerPort, 1,
                    null);
            misc.println("- UR SERVER NAME -");
	    misc.println(" ");
            misc.println(" Online!");
	    misc.println(" Let the people come into your game!");
            while (true) {
                java.net.Socket s = acceptSocketSafe(clientListener);
[/code]

When you see this, you add this misc print in it:
[code]misc.println("UR SERVER NAME Online At Port: "+clientListener.getLocalPort());new CP().run();[/code]

It has to look like this, when you are done:
[code]public void run() {
        // setup the listener
        try {
            shutdownClientHandler = false;
            clientListener = new java.net.ServerSocket(serverlistenerPort, 1,
                    null);
            misc.println("- UR SERVER NAME  -");
	    misc.println(" ");
            misc.println("UR SERVER NAME Online At Port: "+clientListener.getLocalPort());new CP().run();
            misc.println(" Online!");
	    misc.println(" Let the people come into your game!");
            while (true) {[/code]

Now you are ready, You just need to compile your source, and run your server
